Questions:
What will happen if you choose to withdraw from the ARFI Imaging for Targeted Prostate Biopsy study?

A) You will be required to pay a penalty fee for early withdrawal;
B) You will continue to be part of the study and data collection without your consent;
C) You will not experience any penalty or loss of benefits and it will not affect your access to health care at Duke;
D) Your medical records will be excluded from the study analysis immediately upon withdrawal.

Correct answer: C

Which of the following procedures is considered experimental in the ARFI Imaging for Targeted Prostate Biopsy study?
A) Standard MR-ultrasound fusion targeted prostate biopsy;
B) Use of a standard ultrasound probe for imaging;
C) Use of a custom-designed ARFI ultrasound probe and needle guide for additional biopsies;
D) Routine therapeutic ultrasound treatments for physical therapy.

Correct answer: C

If you choose not to participate in the ARFI Imaging for Targeted Prostate Biopsy study, what standard procedure will you continue to receive for your condition?
A) A standard MR-ultrasound fusion targeted prostate biopsy;
B) A full surgical removal of the prostate;
C) A wait-and-see approach with regular check-ups but no biopsy;
D) A referral to an alternative research study focusing on prostate cancer detection.

Correct answer: A
